         <abstract>
            <p>Applying Baker's well-known method and the reduction procedure described by Baker and Davenport, we give a numerical algorithm for finding all solutions of inhomogeneous Thue equations of type $$N_{K/Q}(x + \alpha y + \lambda) = 1$$ in the variables $x, y \in Z$ and $\lambda \in Z_K$ with $K\overset{\lambda}{\smash{\sqcap}} &lt; (\max |x|, |y|))^{1/2}$, where $K = Q(\alpha)$ is a totally real cubic field.</p>
          </abstract>
